{"source":{"uri":"gherkin Features/PaintImageProperties.feature","data":"@image-properties\r\nFeature: Paint Image Properties\r\n    As a user\r\n    I want to modify image properties like dimensions and color mode\r\n    So that I can customize my canvas\r\n\r\n    Background:\r\n        Given I have launched Paint application\r\n\r\n    @smoke @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Open Image Properties dialog\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        Then the Image Properties dialog should be displayed\r\n        And I should see width and height fields\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Change canvas dimensions\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        And I set canvas width to \"1024\"\r\n        And I set canvas height to \"768\"\r\n        And I click OK in Image Properties dialog\r\n        Then the Image Properties dialog should be closed\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Change canvas dimensions with unit\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        And I select \"Pixels\" as unit\r\n        And I set canvas dimensions to \"800\" x \"600\"\r\n        And I apply the image properties\r\n        Then the Image Properties dialog should be closed\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario Outline: Set canvas to common resolutions\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        And I set canvas dimensions to \"<width>\" x \"<height>\" in \"Pixels\"\r\n        And I click OK in Image Properties dialog\r\n        Then the Image Properties dialog should be closed\r\n\r\n        Examples:\r\n        | width | height |\r\n        | 800   | 600    |\r\n        | 1024  | 768    |\r\n        | 1920  | 1080   |\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Change color mode to black and white\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        And I select \"Black and white\" color mode\r\n        And I apply the image properties\r\n        Then the Image Properties dialog should be closed\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Cancel image properties changes\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        And I set canvas dimensions to \"999\" x \"999\"\r\n        And I click Cancel in Image Properties dialog\r\n        Then the Image Properties dialog should be closed\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Reset to default image properties\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        And I set canvas dimensions to \"500\" x \"500\"\r\n        And I reset to default properties\r\n        Then the canvas width should be \"800\"\r\n        And the canvas height should be \"600\"\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Change units between Pixels, Inches, and Centimeters\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        And I select \"Pixels\" as unit\r\n        Then I should see width and height fields\r\n        When I select \"Inches\" as unit\r\n        Then I should see width and height fields\r\n        When I select \"Cm\" as unit\r\n        Then I should see width and height fields\r\n        And I cancel the image properties\r\n\r\n    @image-properties\r\n    Scenario: Verify default canvas dimensions\r\n        When I open Image Properties\r\n        Then the canvas width should be \"800\"\r\n        And the canvas height should be \"600\"\r\n        And I close the Image Properties dialog\r\n","mediaType":"text/x.cucumber.gherkin+plain"}}
